1.title: Monster Sharks
1.plot: MonsterQuest investigates great white sharks whose attacks on humans are on the rise. It follows an expedition in an attempt to tag the first great white in the Atlantic.

2.title: Hillbilly Beast
2.plot: A search in Eastern Kentucky for an elusive creature that is said to make terrifying, wild screams. Investigators look at photographic evidence, and explore the deep woods in an attempt to find the source of these mysterious sounds.

3.title: Giant Pythons in America
3.plot: MonsterQuest goes to Florica in order investigate reports of giant hybrid pythons lurking in areas near the Everglades.

4.title: Giant Killer Bees
4.plot: MonsterQuest looks into reports of Africanized Bees in the southern United States and examines the theory that the bees are adapting to colder weather in spreading further north.

5.title: Mothman
5.plot: MonsterQuest goes to West Virginia to look into the Mothman examining both the original 1967 case and more recent sightings.

6.title: Piranha Invasion
6.plot: MonsterQuest investigates whether a breeding population of Amazonian piranha can survive in the waters of North America.

7.title: Lizard Monster
7.plot: MonsterQuest goes to West Virginia in order to investigate the Flatwoods Monster a reptilian creature that appeared in a strange hovering craft the exuded a noxious gas.

8.title: Sierra Sasquatch
8.plot: MonsterQuest goes to Califonia to investigate claims that a pack of Sasquatch live in the wilderness of Sierra County.

9.title: America's Wolfman
9.plot: MonsterQuest goes to the American Midwest in search of evidence of a half-man/half-wolf and examines a suspicious video purporting to show the creature.

1.title: America's Loch Ness Monster
1.plot: Could there be a prehistoric plesiosaur lurking beneath the waters of Lake Champlain? Examine the mystery surrounding 'Champ'.

2.title: Sasquatch Attack
2.plot: Blood and tissue has been found at a remote cabin damaged by some unknown creature. Could Canada have it's own Sasquatch and are the investigating MonsterQuest crew safe from its attack?

3.title: Giant Squid Found
3.plot: Journey to the Sea of Cortez, Mexico to hunt for squid as large as a whale. Could the legendary Kraken be real?

4.title: Birdzilla
4.plot: MonsterQuest investigates the rash of 'Thunderbird' sightings in Alaska, Texas and Illinois in the 1970's.

5.title: Bigfoot
5.plot: Two expeditions in Washington state are in search of Bigfoot. There is also a look at a recent computer analysis of the famous Patterson film.

6.title: Mutant Canines
6.plot: Pet dogs are being killed by mutant canine creatures in Maine and Minnesota. MonsterQuest analyze photographs and even the body of one beast hit by a car in an attempt to explain what on earth these animals are.

7.title: Lions in the Backyard
7.plot: Witnesses report seeing large black cats in Texas, Minnesota and West Virginia. Could these be mutant mountain lions or is there something else stalking the locals?

8.title: Gigantic Killer Fish
8.plot: From the Amazon to the Arctic Circle, MonsterQuest is on the hunt for monstrous freshwater fish, as big as a boat and large enough to swallow children whole.

9.title: Swamp Beast
9.plot: Examination of the evidence for the Skunk Ape an alleged primate living the the vast swamps of Louisiana and Florida.

10.title: Russia's Killer Apemen
10.plot: Investigation of allegations that Josef Stalin approved of a plan by Soviet scientists to create a human/ape hybrid.

11.title: Unidentified Flying Creatures
11.plot: Mysterious flying creatures known as "flying rods" that are only seen on camera are explored. What are they? Are they creatures from another dimension, are they UFOs, or are they simply optical tricks? You decide.

12.title: The Real Hobbit
12.plot: MonsterQuest travels to Sumatra in Indonesia in search of a small hominid creature known to the locals as Orang Pendak or 'The Man of the Woods'.

13.title: American Werewolf
13.plot: MonsterQuest investigate reports of a frightening dog-man in the Wisconsin and Michigan areas. Could this apparent werewolf actually be a real animal or is there a more sinister explanation?

1.title: Giganto: The Real King Kong
1.plot: A study of the creature which inspired the legend of King Kong, the prehistoric giant ape, Gigantopithecus.

2.title: Mega Hog
2.plot: MonsterQuest teams up with American hog hunters in search of gigantic wild boar.

3.title: Vampire Beast
3.plot: Over 50 years ago there was a spate of mysterious pet and farm animal killings in Bolivia, North Carolina. Now it seems whatever was responsible has returned. Can MonsterQuest uncover the truth behind a creature with a taste for blood?

4.title: Ghosts
4.plot: MonsterQuest visits the Lizzie Borden house in search of it's famous ghosts.

5.title: Ohio Grassman
5.plot: For over a century a Bigfoot-type creature has terrified children in Ohio. Can MonsterQuest discover evidence of the legendary Grassman?

6.title: Giant Killer Snakes
6.plot: Head into the wilds of Venezuela and the Florida Everglades with MonsterQuest as they search for huge man-eating snakes.

7.title: Super Rats
7.plot: Recent archaeological evidence suggests that rats once grew to massive sizes. Could these huge rodents be making a comeback?

8.title: Black Beast of Exmoor
8.plot: MonsterQuest investigates a strange cat-like creature which allegedly is on the prowl in the forests of Great Britain.

9.title: Chupacabra
9.plot: An investigation into reports of a Texan cousin of the infamous 'Goatsucker' - El Chupacabra.

10.title: Legend of the Hairy Beast
10.plot: Both feared and revered by the Native American Indians, whose stories and art about it go back over 1,000 years, the 'Hairy Man' of legend could provide the most promising evidence of a Bigfoot-type creature yet.

11.title: Vampires in America
11.plot: MonsterQuest uncovers a century-long vampire scare in New England in the 1700's. Were there really any vampires about and could there still be some amongst us today?

12.title: Boneless Horror
12.plot: MonsterQuest dives to the bottom of the North Pacific Ocean in an attempt to find a species of giant octopus, large enough to sink a ship.

13.title: Bigfoot in New York
13.plot: The MonsterQuest team go in search of a Bigfoot-type creature in upstate New York, known locally as 'The Monster of Whitehall'.

14.title: China's Wildman
14.plot: MonsterQuest travels to Hubai, a remote Chinese province, in search of a creature covered in reddish-brown hair which the locals have dubbed the 'Wild-Man'.

15.title: Lake Monsters of the North
15.plot: The MonsterQuest team explore both historic and recent sightings of a mysterious eel-like monster in Lake Crescent, Newfoundland, Canada.

16.title: Giant Bear Attack
16.plot: Giant bears once hunted humans in ancient times. Could their smaller modern-day cousins be evolving back to their prehistoric proportions?

17.title: Giant Squid Ambush
17.plot: MonsterQuest returns to the Sea of Cortez in this follow-up episode to 'Giant Squid Found' in the hopes that newer technology might yield greater results.

18.title: Monster Spider
18.plot: Investigation on reports of large desert arachnids in Iraq called Camel Spiders and examines claims about spiders large enough to eat small dogs in Peru.

19.title: Jaws in Illinois
19.plot: From the bayous of Louisiana to the St. Lawrence River in Illinois, MonsterQuest searches for evidence of deadly Bull sharks leaving the oceans and venturing into fresh water.

20.title: Real Dragons
20.plot: MonsterQuest journeys to Australia's Blue Mountains in search of 'Megalania', an extinct giant prehistoric lizard, bigger than it's relative the Komodo Dragon and finds it may not be quite as extinct as people think...

21.title: Sasquatch Attack II
21.plot: MonsterQuest returns to the remote cabin in Northern Ontario, Canada seen in the episode 'Sasquatch Attack', which had previously been attacked by an unknown creature. Will they find evidence of a Bigfoot this time?

1.title: Death of Loch Ness
1.plot: Could the Loch Ness Monster actually be dead and do its remains lie hidden beneath the waters of the lake? MonsterQuest attempts to find out.

2.title: Cattle Killers
2.plot: MonsterQuest try to find out what's been killing and mutilating cattle on the North American plains for over 40 years.

3.title: Swamp Stalker
3.plot: MonsterQuest investigates the real events which inspired the film 'The Legend of Boggy Creek'.

4.title: Devils in New Jersey
4.plot: The MonsterQuest team investigate reports of a half-horse, half-bird creature which has been terrorizing residents of New Jersey for 250 years.

5.title: Gators in the Sewer
5.plot: It's an historic fact that gators were once found beneath the streets of New York. MonsterQuest goes down into the sewers to see if any are still lurking.

6.title: Snowbeast Slaughter
6.plot: MonsterQuest tries to find a creature which has been stalking the Rocky Mountains of Colorado.

7.title: Mega Jaws
7.plot: An expedition searches for the Megalodon a giant prehistoric shark that may still exist of the coast of Mexico's Baja Peninsula.

8.title: Monster Close Encounters
8.plot: MonsterQuest looks at physical evidence of encounters with large humanoid creatures in rural America.

9.title: Lake Demons
9.plot: A dive team visits Lake Okanagan in search of evidence for Ogopogo.

10.title: Sea Monsters
10.plot: MonsterQuest examines video footage taken of a creature in a Florida river.

11.title: Mysterious Ape Island
11.plot: MonsterQuest goes to Vancouver Island in the Pacific Northwest to search for evidence of the legendary Sasquatch.

12.title: Gigantic Killer Fish II
12.plot: MonsterQuest looks at large and dangerous fish species that inhabit our lakes, rivers, and coastlines. It looks at giant catfish, freshwater pike, giant lake trout, and alligator gar.

13.title: Isle of the Lost Tiger
13.plot: MonsterQuest goes to Tasmania in an effort to track down the thylacine which is thought to have gone extinct in the 1930s.

14.title: Killer Jellyfish
14.plot: The most venomous animals in the sea may be smarter than we know. The Monsterquest team led by Dale Pearson travels to Australia to research and find new information on the deadly box jellyfish.

15.title: Flying Monsters
15.plot: MonsterQuest goes to Papua New Guinea in an effort to track down a prehistoric flying monster.

16.title: The Curse of the Monkey Man
16.plot: MonsterQuest goes to India in order to look into reports of an ape-like creature called the "Mande Barung".

17.title: Killer Crocs
17.plot: MonsterQuest goes to India and the Florida Everglades to investigate claims of giant crocodiles.

18.title: The Last Dinosaur
18.plot: MonsterQuest goes to the jungles of Central Africa in search of Mokele-mbembe which is believed by some to be a living relic of the dinosaurs.

19.title: Critical Evidence
19.plot: MonsterQuest looks at five key pieces of evidence for the Sasquatch: the Patterson footage, the Freeman footage, the Cripplefoot tracks, the mid-tarsal break, and maps of sighting density.

20.title: The Real Cujo
20.plot: MonsterQuest looks at feral dogs packs in the United States and examines whether such packs pose a risk to human beings.

21.title: Terror from the Sky
21.plot: MonsterQuest goes to Mexico to investigate the phenomena of Unidentified Flying Humanoids.

22.title: Killer Chimps in America
22.plot: MonsterQuest looks into reports of chimpanzees on the loose in the United States.

23.title: Tigers in the Suburbs
23.plot: MonsterQuest looks into claims that large cats are on the prowl in the forests of the United States.

24.title: The Real Moby Dick
24.plot: MonsterQuest goes to the Azores in order to look for an albino sperm whale and investigate the theory that such an animal would be hostile.

25.title: Abominable Snowman
25.plot: The MonsterQuest lads are out and about on their little discoveries looking for something that doesn't exist.

imdb.title: Monsterquest
plot: The series explores strange and unknown creatures that have been allegedly spotted by witnesses in various parts of the country and the world.::arorashadow_2003
